LOESS reference implementation
------------------------------
packages/core/src/stats/loess.ts adapts its structure (the sorted
nearest-neighbor window walk and the tricube kernel) from SveltePlot's
`src/regression/loess.ts` (ISC License, Copyright (c) Gregor Aisch and
SveltePlot contributors), which is itself adapted from:

  - d3-regression, Copyright (c) Harry Stevens (MIT License)
    https://github.com/HarryStevens/d3-regression
  - science.js, Copyright (c) Jason Davies (BSD-3-Clause License)
    https://github.com/jasondavies/science.js
  - vega-statistics, Copyright (c) University of Washington Interactive
    Data Lab (BSD-3-Clause License)
    https://github.com/vega/vega

The ggsvelte implementation is substantially rewritten for parity with R's
stats::loess (span-based neighborhoods, configurable polynomial degree,
prediction at arbitrary points, and exact operator statistics for the
confidence band); no verbatim code from the above projects remains, but the
algorithmic lineage is acknowledged here per their license terms and the
project plan.

Binning, boxplot, density, and summary algorithms are independent ports of
the published ggplot2 (MIT) and R (GPL — algorithms only, no code copied)
semantics, verified against R-generated fixtures; see
docs/decisions/0010-m2-stats-notes.md.
